  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Geneva Study Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cverse2",
        "text": "{1} And he opened his mouth, and taught them, saying,",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cverse3",
            "text": "{1}",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " And he opened his mouth, and taught them, saying,",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(1) Christ teaches that the greatest joy and happiness is not in the conveniences and pleasures of this life, but is laid up in heaven for those who willingly rest in the good will and pleasure of God, and endeavour to profit all men, although they are cruelly vexed and troubled by those of the world, because they will not adapt themselves to their ways.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
